# CODEOWNERS — security review routing for Corvus
#
# Implements the "structured PR + code review" half of the GitHub-workflow
# proposal. Any change to the paths below REQUIRES security review before merge.
# Pair this with branch protection on `main` that requires Code Owner review and
# the certification workflow status checks. CODEOWNERS routes review but does
# not itself enforce it.
#
# Security owner: @asifdotpy (Asif, OAI). Add Lucas/Alexander as owners for
# their non-security paths (corvus/mvp, corvus/infrastructure/repositories
# non-auth, apps/, openapi/) once this PR lands.

# Protect the ownership policy, security-governance documents, and required
# certification workflow from unreviewed rerouting or check-name preservation.
